Lion Capital Plans to Split Young’s Seafood Owner, FT Reports

-- B y   K a r i   L u n d g r e n
-- 
2011-10-15T08:59:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-15/lion-capital-plans-to-split-young-s-seafood-owner-ft-reports.html
Lion Capital, a private equity
company that focuses on  consumer goods , is considering breaking
up frozen-food company Findus Group to focus on U.K. operations,
the FT reported.  The private-equity company is in talks with two bidders to
sell Findus’s Nordic division, valued at as much as 1 billion
euros ($1.38 billion), the newspaper said, citing people close
to the situation.  Buyers have also approached Lion about acquiring Findus’s
French division, the FT said, adding that the private equity
company is not considering a sale of the unit. Lion declined to
comment, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kari Lundgren in London at 
